    "He taught in Paris, 1959-1961, and then, at the invitation of <a href=\"/panofskye\">Erwin Panofsky</a>, in Princeton, N. J. at the Institute for Advanced Study in 1961.": [],
    "In Princeton, Sauerl\u00e4nder developed his theory for the sculpture at Ch\u00e2lons-sur-Marne, which he presented at the 1961 International Congress of Art History in New York.": [
        [
            68,
